Yes, you can, however pay close attention to the block 

 

    $JustAWebGLObject:
        {
    
        },

Consider it as a class in C# called `JustAWebGLObject`, you can define functions, variables etc inside it.

        $JustAWebGLObject:
        {
            ClassFunction: function()
            {

            },
        },

You can call `ClassFunction` from vue using 

    JustAWebGLObject.ClassFunction();

What about global functions outside the object `JustAWebGLObject`  ?

Global functions like your `SendToJavscript`, unity compiles them during build into the global `UnityLoader.js` and prefixes them with an underscore `_`  so to call this global function from Vue, or  any other javascript library, or even from another function in the same jslib file, you need to prefix its name with an `_`

Simply call `_SendToJavscript(somestring);`

However, note that this function accepts a pointer from C# coming to javascript, but if another javascript function calls it and passes it a string, it will be passed as a string, so you would need to have your function handle being called from javascript and from C#, something like

    SendToJavascript: function(pointer,actualString)
    {
        var str = &quot;&quot;;
        if(actualString)
           str = actualString;
        else
           str = Pointer_stringify(pointer);
       
    },

**From C#** `SendToJavascript(&quot;hello&quot;,null); // First parameter will be sent as a pointer.`


**From Javascript** `_SendToJavascript(0, &quot;hello&quot;);`

